				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Beaker wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">so you can add/rem maybe 3 players per second
<br />

<br />
86,400 seconds in a day, so about 29,000 characters in a day</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Well, maybe my math is wrong, but isn't that 250k or so characters a day? <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
Anyway, if you (ma2885) are really interested in setting this up, you'd basically need a multi-threaded bot that allowed concurrent connections to communicate with each other. 
<br />

<br />
If you would like to know what I would do, I'd first set up around 15 bots on RK1, 10 bots on RK2, and 5 bots on RK3. (if I recall correctly, there's a maximum of 32 characters per server, as far as chat-characters go, but my memory may be wrong.) Each bot would poll the server, like Beaker mentioned, by querying a members database (I have one available at <a href="http://www.aoraids.com/members.zip" target="_blank">http://www.aoraids.com/members.zip</a> if you're looking for one) and adding / removing everyone to receive player status. When you find a user that is online, you add them to a buddylist that keeps them on it (managed by a few dedicated bots, or it could be totally dynamic and simply use available character space) and store them in that buddylist until they logoff. That would keep accurate logoff statistics. As for logins, I'd keep track of the frequency of the logins and have a database that stores this frequency. The players that connect the most are polled the most often, but players who rarely are polled less often. 
<br />

<br />
Although it wouldn't be "real time", it would be somewhat accurate. There are around 225k existing characters (in my members DB, anyway), and you could, with 30 bots, poll the entire Members DB in around 40 minutes (255k players / 30 bots / 3 per second / 60 seconds).
<br />

<br />
In other words, it's certainly possible, though a lot of work, and really isn't worth it. Buddylists are the only way to keep track of players information because Funcom wont release online statistics like most other MMORPGs. 
<br />

<br />
-Ethernal</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
